defs.name: VariedSection

defs.docs:
An object that contains all the info to render a varied section of text. That is one including
 many parts with differing fonts/scales/colors bowing to a single layout.

defs.name: with_info
defs.value: fn (&self, index: usize, info: GlyphInfo<'a>) -> Self
defs.docs:
Returns a clone info that has marked text up to `index` as processed, and
 `GlyphInfo` at index as input `info`

defs.name: GlyphInfo
defs.docs:
A specialised view on a [`Section`](struct.Section.html) for the purposes of calculating
 glyph positions. Used by a [`GlyphPositioner`](trait.GlyphPositioner.html).

defs.name: text
defs.docs:
Section text, use [`remaining_chars()`](struct.GlyphInfo.html#method.remaining_chars)
 instead in order to respect skip settings, ie in leftover payloads.

defs.name: remaining_chars
defs.docs:
Returns a unicode normalized char iterator, that respects the skipped chars
 that have already been already processed

defs.name: remaining_char_indices
defs.docs:
Returns a unicode normalized (byte_index, char) iterator, that respects the
 skipped chars that have already been already processed

defs.name: skip
defs.docs:
Returns a new GlyphInfo instance whose
 [`remaining_chars()`](struct.GlyphInfo.html#method.remaining_chars)
 method will skip additional chars (not bytes!)

defs.name: substring
defs.docs: Returns a substring reference according the current skip value

defs.name: RemainingNormCharIndices
defs.docs: `char_indices` style iterator for skipped normalized chars

defs.name: GlyphPositioner
defs.docs:
Logic to calculate glyph positioning based on [`Font`](type.Font.html) and
 [`GlyphInfo`](struct.GlyphInfo.html)

defs.name: calculate_glyphs
defs.value: fn <'a, 'font, G> (&self, font: &HashMap<FontId, Font<'font>>, section: G) -> Vec<GlyphedSectionText<'font>>
defs.docs:
Calculate a sequence of positioned glyphs to render. Custom implementations should always
 return the same result when called with the same arguments. If not consider disabling
 [`cache_glyph_positioning`](struct.GlyphBrushBuilder.html#method.cache_glyph_positioning).

defs.name: bounds_rect
defs.docs:
Return a rectangle according to the requested render position and bounds appropriate
 for the glyph layout.

defs.name: SingleLine
defs.docs:
Renders a single line from left-to-right according to the inner alignment.
 Hard breaking will end the line, partially hitting the width bound will end the line.

defs.name: Wrap
defs.docs:
Renders multiple lines from left-to-right according to the inner alignment.
 Hard breaking characters will cause advancement to another line.
 A characters hitting the width bound will also cause another line to start.

defs.name: Layout
defs.docs: Built-in [`GlyphPositioner`](trait.GlyphPositioner.html) implementations.

defs.name: h_align
defs.docs: Returns an identical `Layout` but with the input `h_align`

defs.name: v_align
defs.docs: Returns an identical `Layout` but with the input `v_align`

defs.name: line_breaker
defs.docs: Returns an identical `Layout` but with the input `line_breaker`

defs.name: Left
defs.docs:
Leftmost character is immediately to the right of the render position.
Bounds start from the render position and advance rightwards.

defs.name: Center
defs.docs:
Leftmost & rightmost characters are equidistant to the render position.
Bounds start from the render position and advance equally left & right.

defs.name: Right
defs.docs:
Rightmost character is immetiately to the left of the render position.
Bounds start from the render position and advance leftwards.

defs.name: HorizontalAlign
defs.docs: Describes horizontal alignment preference for positioning & bounds.

defs.name: Top
defs.docs: Characters/bounds start underneath the render position and progress downwards

defs.name: VerticalAlign
defs.docs:
Describes vertical alignment preference for positioning & bounds. Currently a placeholder
 for future functionality.

defs.name: HardBreak
defs.docs:
leftover text after a new hard line break, indicated by the
 [`LineBreaker`](trait.LineBreaker.html)

defs.name: OutOfWidthBound
defs.docs: text that would fall outside of the horizontal bound

defs.name: OutOfHeightBound
defs.docs:
text that would fall fully outside the vertical bound
 note: does not include hidden text within a layout
 for example a `_` character hidden but between visible characters would be ignored

defs.name: LayoutLeftover
defs.docs: Container for glyphs leftover/unable to fit in a layout and/or within render bounds

defs.name: Soft
defs.docs: Soft line break (offset).

defs.name: Hard
defs.docs: Hard line break (offset).

defs.name: LineBreak
defs.docs: Indicator that a character is a line break, soft or hard. Includes the offset position.

defs.name: offset
defs.docs: Returns the offset of the line break, the index after the breaking character.

defs.name: LineBreaker
defs.docs:
Producer of a [`LineBreak`](enum.LineBreak.html) iterator. Used to allow to the
 [`Layout`](enum.Layout.html) to be line break aware in a generic way.

defs.name: UnicodeLineBreaker
defs.docs:
LineBreaker that follows Unicode Standard Annex #14. That effectively means it
 wraps words in a way that should work for most cases.

defs.name: AnyCharLineBreaker
defs.docs:
LineBreaker that soft breaks on any character, and hard breaks similarly to
 UnicodeLineBreaker.

defs.name: add_font

defs.name: initial_cache_size
defs.docs:
Initial size of 2D texture used as a gpu cache, pixels (width, height).
 The GPU cache will dynamically quadruple in size whenever the current size
 is insufficient.

defs.name: gpu_cache_scale_tolerance
defs.docs:
Sets the maximum allowed difference in scale used for judging whether to reuse an
 existing glyph in the GPU cache.

defs.name: gpu_cache_position_tolerance
defs.docs:
Sets the maximum allowed difference in subpixel position used for judging whether
 to reuse an existing glyph in the GPU cache. Anything greater than or equal to
 1.0 means "don't care".

defs.name: cache_glyph_positioning
defs.docs:
Sets whether perform the calculation of glyph positioning according to the layout
 every time, or use a cached result if the input `Section` and `GlyphPositioner` are the
 same hash as a previous call.

defs.name: cache_glyph_drawing
defs.docs: Sets optimising drawing by reusing the last draw requesting an identical draw queue.

defs.name: depth_test
defs.docs: Sets the depth test to use on the text section **z** values.

defs.name: texture_filter_method
defs.docs: Sets the texture filtering method.

defs.name: GlyphBrush
defs.docs:
Object allowing glyph drawing, containing cache state. Manages glyph positioning cacheing,
 glyph draw caching & efficient GPU texture cache updating and re-sizing on demand.

Queues a section/layout to be drawn by the next call of
 [`draw_queued`](struct.GlyphBrush.html#method.draw_queued). Can be called multiple times
 to queue multiple sections for drawing.

defs.name: queue
